00:01:01.680 --> 00:01:05.730
Pretty Derby

00:02:12.880 --> 00:02:16.400
Wow, you're on the cover of 
about every paper, McQueen.

00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:19.490
This is awesome, McQueen! 
You've got all eyes on you.

00:02:16.900 --> 00:02:21.910
{\an1}Episode 7
A Blessed Name

00:02:19.490 --> 00:02:23.890
I'm glad, but I must admit, it's a bit 
embarrassing to receive so much attention.

00:02:23.890 --> 00:02:26.760
"Rice Shower's management 
declares her imminent victory.

00:02:26.760 --> 00:02:28.390
'On a clear day, she will win.'"

00:02:28.390 --> 00:02:31.840
True enough. I think the only competition 
you have in long-distance racing right now

00:02:31.840 --> 00:02:33.150
is Rice Shower.

00:02:33.150 --> 00:02:35.720
It says that her time during 
the last three furlongs

00:02:35.720 --> 00:02:38.240
of the Kikkashou was better than yours.

00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:40.910
There's more to racing than segment times.

00:02:42.160 --> 00:02:45.690
But fair enough. I'd be glad to take her on.

00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:49.330
I didn't let Teio have the Spring plaque.

00:02:49.330 --> 00:02:51.530
And it will be mine again.

00:02:52.200 --> 00:02:56.420
Let's introduce the star horse girls 
going into the Spring Tennoushou.

00:02:56.420 --> 00:02:58.770
It's fair to say that the 
spotlight is shining on

00:02:56.420 --> 00:03:00.630
A CLOSE LOOK AT THE HORSE GIRLS RUNNING IN THE SPRING TENNOUSHOU!

00:02:58.770 --> 00:03:01.950
Mejiro McQueen, who is hoping to win 
the race for a third consecutive time.

00:03:00.630 --> 00:03:04.890
A CLOSE LOOK AT THE HORSE GIRLS RUNNING IN THE SPRING TENNOUSHOU!

00:03:01.950 --> 00:03:04.900
People are calling her the best active racer,
and they're not exaggerating.

00:03:04.900 --> 00:03:09.700
Next is Rice Shower, who foiled 
Mihono Bourbon's attempt at the Triple Crown.

00:03:09.700 --> 00:03:11.770
Will she put an end to another 
attempt to make history?

00:03:10.270 --> 00:03:11.770
A CLOSE LOOK AT THE HORSE GIRLS RUNNING IN THE SPRING TENNOUSHOU!

00:03:12.380 --> 00:03:14.020
Rice Shower's running too, huh?

00:03:14.280 --> 00:03:16.270
This is McQueen's shot at 
a third consecutive win.

00:03:16.270 --> 00:03:17.640
Here's hoping she doesn't ruin it.

00:03:17.640 --> 00:03:18.780
Tell me about it.

00:03:20.340 --> 00:03:23.740
Rice Shower took first place 
at the Nikkei Sho as well.

00:03:23.740 --> 00:03:27.240
A CLOSE LOOK AT THE HORSE GIRLS RUNNING IN THE SPRING TENNOUSHOU!

00:03:23.740 --> 00:03:27.240
She's bound to be in good shape 
heading towards the Spring Tennoushou.

00:03:26.350 --> 00:03:27.240
Hey, hey, hey!

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:29.450
Is it me, or is Rice looking 
real strong lately?!

00:03:29.450 --> 00:03:30.940
She's been working hard.

00:03:29.450 --> 00:03:36.210
Friendship • Effort • Victory

00:03:30.940 --> 00:03:34.220
I think she's got her sights 
set on taking McQueen down.

