00:03:36.880 --> 00:03:39.890
In her last race in the G2, 
she managed to beat Rice Shower.

00:03:39.890 --> 00:03:41.300
Expectations for her will be high.

00:03:42.960 --> 00:03:45.050
She did beat Rice, after all.

00:03:45.840 --> 00:03:47.840
You were all there rooting for me, remember?!

00:03:48.960 --> 00:03:51.310
We're gonna do some godrunning 
at the Tennoushou, too!

00:03:51.310 --> 00:03:52.850
I'm down to clown with that!

00:03:52.850 --> 00:03:55.470
I think we might've figured 
out the trick to outrunning.

00:03:55.470 --> 00:03:57.980
For real, though! It's like, you 
gotta run hella good, right?

00:03:57.980 --> 00:04:01.840
Coming around the second corner, it's
 Daitaku Helios and Mejiro Palmer in the lead!

00:04:01.840 --> 00:04:03.740
Yet again, we see the two 
of them setting the pace!

00:04:03.740 --> 00:04:04.300
It's me!

00:04:04.300 --> 00:04:04.930
No, me!

00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:05.460
It's me!

00:04:05.460 --> 00:04:06.650
No, me!

00:04:06.650 --> 00:04:10.120
And Mejiro Palmer and Daitaku Helios
 have fallen apart!

00:04:10.510 --> 00:04:13.460
We didn't manage to stay out in 
front during the Fall Tennoushou.

00:04:13.670 --> 00:04:16.210
We're now on the back half of the race!

00:04:16.210 --> 00:04:18.930
Mejiro Palmer and Daitaku Helios are 
outrunning the others by a big margin!

00:04:18.930 --> 00:04:21.800
There are over ten lengths between 
the two of them and third place!

00:04:21.800 --> 00:04:23.970
The others will have to pick 
up the pace to close this gap!

00:04:23.970 --> 00:04:24.710
It's me!

00:04:23.970 --> 00:04:26.340
It doesn't look like anyone is 
going to come close, though!

00:04:24.710 --> 00:04:25.240
No, me!

00:04:25.240 --> 00:04:25.800
It's me!

00:04:25.800 --> 00:04:26.970
No, me!

00:04:28.220 --> 00:04:29.980
You can take it from here!

00:04:29.970 --> 00:04:32.470
We're BFFs!

00:04:33.200 --> 00:04:33.580
<font size="21" color="#4dbb71">Nice Nature</font>

00:04:34.570 --> 00:04:37.680
But we ran like whoa at the Arima Kinen!

00:04:38.480 --> 00:04:40.000
Rice!

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:42.590
Looking forward to running with 
you in the next race, Rice!

00:04:42.590 --> 00:04:43.990
Huh?

00:04:46.240 --> 00:04:47.550
What's with her?

00:04:47.550 --> 00:04:48.990
Not sure...

00:04:51.990 --> 00:04:55.000
Intent to Ultim-Outrun!!

00:04:51.990 --> 00:04:55.000
McQueen  Setting Her Sights on a Third Consecutive Win

00:04:52.890 --> 00:04:55.000
Machikane Tannhäuser and Mejiro Palmer in Top Shape!

00:04:56.750 --> 00:04:58.750
{\an9}Rice Shower's Management
<font color="#438a92">Confident in Her Ability
 to Upset Mejiro McQueen!</font>

00:04:56.750 --> 00:04:58.750
Will the <font size="25">Assassin in Black 
</font><font size="15">Thwart Another Major Accomplishment?!</font>

00:04:58.750 --> 00:05:00.250
Will the Assassin in Black
 Thwart Another Major Accomplishment?!

00:05:00.730 --> 00:05:02.310
Rice Shower-san?

00:05:04.300 --> 00:05:05.860
I was hoping to speak with you.

00:05:06.880 --> 00:05:09.000
I saw the feature you were in.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:11.740
You seem certain you'll be able to win.

00:05:11.740 --> 00:05:15.270
Consider the challenge accepted. 
Let's have a good race, shall we?

00:05:19.330 --> 00:05:21.320
I'm not running in the Tennoushou.

00:05:22.180 --> 00:05:24.860
I don't want to race anymore!

00:05:24.860 --> 00:05:26.040
Hey, wait—

00:05:31.460 --> 00:05:33.870
McQueen-san is so cool!

00:05:33.870 --> 00:05:36.200
A third championship! That'd be great to see.

00:05:36.200 --> 00:05:38.120
I'd love to see it happen!

00:05:38.120 --> 00:05:39.220
It's gonna be great!

00:05:39.220 --> 00:05:40.140
Right?

00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:42.340
What?

00:05:42.340 --> 00:05:43.600
Is this for real?

00:05:43.600 --> 00:05:45.100
Unbelievable...

00:05:46.050 --> 00:05:48.010
It's such a shame.

00:05:55.220 --> 00:05:58.650
No one wants me around.

00:05:59.190 --> 00:06:01.020
Wait, Rice isn't running?

00:06:01.020 --> 00:06:03.500
She doesn't seem to want to run anymore.

00:06:04.120 --> 00:06:08.500
It's probably some scheme to get you 
to drop your guard before the race.

00:06:04.220 --> 00:06:06.520
Did something happen to her?

00:06:06.520 --> 00:06:08.830
Her entry is still listed...

00:06:08.500 --> 00:06:10.430
That sounds like a plan <i>you'd</i> come up with.

00:06:08.830 --> 00:06:10.780
So it's probably something personal.

00:06:10.430 --> 00:06:13.330
Excuse me?! I always run fair and square!

00:06:10.780 --> 00:06:13.600
Hey, the less competition, the better.

00:06:13.330 --> 00:06:14.430
Do you, now?

00:06:13.600 --> 00:06:15.080
You'll have an even easier time taking it.

00:06:14.430 --> 00:06:17.130
You're the one who tries to dupe 
people by faking like you got a cold!

00:06:16.090 --> 00:06:17.410
What's wrong?

00:06:17.130 --> 00:06:18.440
I do no such thing!

00:06:17.410 --> 00:06:21.950
It's a bit disappointing. I had 
heard she was looking strong.

00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:20.510
You're the one who pulls that 
"maybe I'll run, maybe not" scheme!

00:06:20.510 --> 00:06:21.950
It's not a scheme!

00:06:21.950 --> 00:06:23.790
Worrying about someone else 
won't get you anywhere.

00:06:21.950 --> 00:06:24.660
That just makes you a liar!

00:06:23.790 --> 00:06:25.680
You should focus on your training.

00:06:24.660 --> 00:06:26.560
I am not!

00:06:25.680 --> 00:06:27.150
I suppose...

00:06:27.150 --> 00:06:29.300
I'm going to ask her what's going on.

00:06:29.630 --> 00:06:30.320
Teio?

00:06:30.320 --> 00:06:34.060
You're not gonna be able to focus on 
your training with this bugging you.

00:06:34.560 --> 00:06:37.160
Leave this to your team leader!

00:06:38.750 --> 00:06:40.360
We'll go, too!

00:06:40.360 --> 00:06:41.130
Right?

00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:42.060
Sounds good.

00:06:44.750 --> 00:06:47.090
I appreciate it, everyone.

00:06:53.470 --> 00:06:54.830
Found ya, Rice!

00:06:55.190 --> 00:06:56.890
Nice weather today, huh?

00:06:56.890 --> 00:06:59.890
Makes you want to get out 
there and run hard, right?

00:06:59.890 --> 00:07:01.210
I-I guess so...

00:07:01.210 --> 00:07:05.430
But if you run too much, it makes 
fixing up the track a lot of work!

00:07:05.430 --> 00:07:07.960
Huh? She's not asking about the Tennoushou?

00:07:07.960 --> 00:07:10.800
I actually wanted to ask 
you about the Tennoushou—

00:07:11.540 --> 00:07:13.300
Hey, wait!

00:07:19.270 --> 00:07:22.070
Look at this! I'm great at 
touching the bottom of my feet!

00:07:22.070 --> 00:07:25.440
You gonna enter the Spring Ten? 
I bet it'd be a lot of fun!

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:28.070
Probably as much fun as stretching like this!

00:07:28.070 --> 00:07:31.070
I actually hold a record in flexibility!

00:07:34.700 --> 00:07:35.820
Rice...

00:07:35.820 --> 00:07:37.450
About the Spring Ten...

00:07:38.970 --> 00:07:39.660
Hey!

00:07:42.490 --> 00:07:43.330
This is kinda...

00:07:43.330 --> 00:07:45.170
This looks like a job for me.

00:07:53.630 --> 00:07:55.550
I'm counting on you, Spe-chan!

00:07:55.550 --> 00:07:59.760
Rice Shower. What a lovely name! I'm a fan.

00:07:59.760 --> 00:08:01.560
Especially the "rice" part.

00:08:04.550 --> 00:08:05.560
It didn't work.

00:08:05.560 --> 00:08:07.740
I'm not sure what you were 
trying to accomplish!

00:08:07.740 --> 00:08:10.690
I guess we'll have to 
try the direct approach!

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:22.080
Wh-Who are you?

00:08:22.080 --> 00:08:25.880
Scarlet! Vodka! Spe! Get 'er, girls!

00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:27.630
Right, Gold Ship-san!

00:08:27.890 --> 00:08:29.290
It's Spica!

00:08:31.590 --> 00:08:33.640
Heave-ho, heave-ho!

00:08:33.640 --> 00:08:36.250
Um... wh-what is this?

00:08:36.250 --> 00:08:38.100
Sorry about this, Rice.

00:08:38.100 --> 00:08:41.970
McQueen told us you weren't 
going to run in the Tennoushou.

00:08:42.500 --> 00:08:45.020
Would you tell us about it?

00:08:47.630 --> 00:08:50.190
Will you let me go if I do?

00:08:52.080 --> 00:08:53.640
Because there's no point.

00:08:54.640 --> 00:08:55.740
What do you mean?

00:08:57.360 --> 00:08:59.900
Because no one wants me around.

00:09:01.910 --> 00:09:06.590
Ever since I was little, I used to look 
up to things that were glamorous.

00:09:04.750 --> 00:09:07.120
The two of them were blessed
with a rice shower to bring them good fortune!

00:09:08.440 --> 00:09:11.130
The two of them were blessed
with a rice shower to bring them good fortune!

00:09:11.130 --> 00:09:14.130
The Magic of Happiness

00:09:14.130 --> 00:09:16.380
There are 100 meters to go! 
First place has a tiny lead!

00:09:16.380 --> 00:09:18.210
Number 8, Rice Shower, is in 
front by a small margin!

00:09:18.210 --> 00:09:20.890
And Rice Shower crosses the 
goal with her lead intact!

00:09:20.890 --> 00:09:25.120
Rice Shower has done a fine 
job of winning her debut race!

00:09:25.120 --> 00:09:28.300
I was so glad when I won my first race...

00:09:29.060 --> 00:09:31.300
And everyone was really happy.

00:09:31.770 --> 00:09:34.230
It made running seem like so much fun.

00:09:34.230 --> 00:09:37.780
I thought that even someone 
like me could be glamorous.

00:09:37.780 --> 00:09:39.970
She's striking an imposing figure!

00:09:39.970 --> 00:09:43.740
Mihono Bourbon manages to outrun the 
entire pack as she crosses the goal!

00:09:43.740 --> 00:09:46.860
She wins the Satsukishou while undefeated!

00:09:47.990 --> 00:09:51.640
Bourbon-san was so dazzling 
when she won the Satsukishou...

00:09:51.640 --> 00:09:56.100
So I decided I wanted 
to be like her someday.

00:09:56.100 --> 00:09:58.930
Mihono Bourbon is in the lead! 
It's looking like she has this race won!

00:09:59.340 --> 00:10:01.800
I wanted to catch up with 
the person I idolized.

00:10:01.800 --> 00:10:04.800
I wanted to win a race, 
and be like Bourbon-san.

00:10:07.980 --> 00:10:10.860
And then, at the Kikkashou, 
it finally happened..

00:10:11.550 --> 00:10:13.070
Mihono Bourbon is in the lead!

00:10:13.070 --> 00:10:16.090
Rice Shower is closing the gap! 
Mihono Bourbon still has a faint lead!

00:10:16.090 --> 00:10:18.850
But Rice Shower moves up on the outside!
 Rice Shower passes her!

00:10:18.850 --> 00:10:21.780
Rice Shower has the lead! 
And she clears the goal!

00:10:21.340 --> 00:10:21.780
Kikkashou

00:10:21.780 --> 00:10:24.690
Mihono Bourbon's Triple Crown 
will remain incomplete!

00:10:24.690 --> 00:10:28.090
The winning horse girl of the 
Kikkashou is Rice Shower!

00:10:28.520 --> 00:10:30.110
Wait, what?

00:10:30.110 --> 00:10:30.990
What the heck?

00:10:30.990 --> 00:10:31.860
Seriously?

00:10:31.860 --> 00:10:33.840
I wanted to see a Triple Crown.

00:10:33.840 --> 00:10:35.000
Why?

00:10:40.070 --> 00:10:43.460
Nobody wanted me to win.

00:10:44.700 --> 00:10:46.810
Why didn't Bourbon win?

00:10:46.810 --> 00:10:50.030
I destroyed Bourbon-san 
and her fans' dreams.

00:10:50.440 --> 00:10:52.020
Everyone was sad.

00:10:54.820 --> 00:11:00.390
Now everyone is looking forward to 
McQueen-san winning a third Spring Tennoushou.

00:11:00.390 --> 00:11:04.550
Even if I enter and win, 
no one will be happy.

00:11:04.550 --> 00:11:06.840
I'll just make everyone miserable.

00:11:07.240 --> 00:11:11.000
Me, whose name is supposed to 
represent something happy.

00:11:11.480 --> 00:11:12.450
That's... really heavy.

00:11:12.450 --> 00:11:15.090
So I won't be running anymore.

00:11:15.090 --> 00:11:16.000
Rice?

00:11:16.630 --> 00:11:19.250
Please, leave me alone.

00:11:22.270 --> 00:11:23.450
Rice...

00:11:30.900 --> 00:11:32.520
I had no idea.

00:11:32.520 --> 00:11:34.650
I understand how she feels!

00:11:34.650 --> 00:11:36.670
She worked so hard on her racing,

00:11:36.670 --> 00:11:39.000
so it has to be frustrating for no 
one to recognize what she accomplished!

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:43.760
True enough, Rice's Kikkashou win is 
something that should have been celebrated.

00:11:43.760 --> 00:11:44.650
But...

00:11:45.260 --> 00:11:47.840
I believe using that as a reason 
to turn away from racing is,

00:11:47.840 --> 00:11:50.300
for a horse girl, mistaken.

00:11:53.440 --> 00:11:54.860
McQueen...

00:11:56.190 --> 00:11:57.090
Okay!

00:11:57.780 --> 00:12:01.590
I'll try and convince Rice to run after all.

00:12:01.590 --> 00:12:04.200
Just don't regret this, okay?

00:12:04.200 --> 00:12:06.360
I would never.

00:12:06.360 --> 00:12:10.220
Besides, I find it vexing to 
have Rice taking me so lightly.

00:12:11.020 --> 00:12:13.730
"No one will be happy if I win"?

00:12:13.730 --> 00:12:16.400
She's so certain of her victory,
 before even running.

00:12:16.820 --> 00:12:17.730
Now that you mention it...

00:12:20.730 --> 00:12:23.990
Please take care of things with Rice, Leader.

