00:13:26.300 --> 00:13:29.150
Mihono Bourbon's Triple Crown 
will remain incomplete!

00:13:29.150 --> 00:13:32.310
The winning horse girl of the 
Kikkashou is Rice Shower!

00:13:33.790 --> 00:13:35.270
By losing the Kikkashou,

00:13:35.270 --> 00:13:38.770
I was unable to fulfill Master's 
request that I win a Triple Crown.

00:13:39.110 --> 00:13:42.070
I may have been anxious to 
redeem myself as a result.

00:13:43.130 --> 00:13:44.120
Expectations...

00:13:44.800 --> 00:13:48.660
My goal is to win the Triple Crown
 undefeated, just like you!

00:13:48.660 --> 00:13:50.530
So I have to win!

00:13:52.010 --> 00:13:54.170
Right. I'll be looking forward to it.

00:13:56.940 --> 00:13:58.260
It was the same for me.

00:13:58.750 --> 00:14:01.310
If I hadn't gotten injured, 
and had won the Triple Crown,

00:14:01.310 --> 00:14:04.050
I might've gotten to see the Prez smile.

00:14:04.330 --> 00:14:05.710
I can relate.

00:14:05.710 --> 00:14:10.270
I was hoping to see my Master's smile, 
something I've never seen before.

00:14:11.830 --> 00:14:15.180
Sorry about your Triple Crown, Bourbon.

00:14:15.180 --> 00:14:16.740
Likewise, Teio-san.

00:14:18.060 --> 00:14:21.880
But because I was unable 
to achieve a Triple Crown,

00:14:21.880 --> 00:14:24.170
I was able to find a new reason for racing.

00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:26.900
Rice Shower.

00:14:26.900 --> 00:14:27.960
Rice?

00:14:27.960 --> 00:14:31.270
Yes. The only horse girl to ever defeat me...

00:14:31.270 --> 00:14:33.450
The person who kept me 
from reaching my dream.

00:14:34.030 --> 00:14:37.580
She may be the first competitor 
I've felt I could call my rival.

00:14:39.300 --> 00:14:42.270
Listen... about Rice...

00:14:42.270 --> 00:14:43.500
Yes?

00:14:43.500 --> 00:14:44.330
Beef steak!

00:14:44.330 --> 00:14:45.030
Beef steak!

00:14:45.030 --> 00:14:45.790
Beef steak!

00:14:45.790 --> 00:14:46.460
Beef steak!

00:14:46.460 --> 00:14:47.270
Beef steak!

00:14:47.270 --> 00:14:48.090
Beef steak!

00:14:48.090 --> 00:14:48.840
Beef steak!

00:14:48.840 --> 00:14:49.840
Beef steak!

00:14:50.720 --> 00:14:53.490
T-Teio-san?! What is it now?!

00:14:53.490 --> 00:14:57.150
You don't have to be so scared! 
I'm not gonna do anything.

00:14:57.150 --> 00:14:58.090
Rice...

00:14:58.680 --> 00:15:00.560
B-Bourbon-san?!

00:15:02.320 --> 00:15:04.810
You apparently don't intend 
to run in the Tennoushou?

00:15:07.070 --> 00:15:10.810
You've gotta do something to convince 
her to run in the Tennoushou, Bourbon.

00:15:10.810 --> 00:15:13.810
I bet she'll listen to you!

00:15:13.810 --> 00:15:17.920
Leave this to me. There is a method 
I've learned from my Master.

00:15:17.920 --> 00:15:18.940
Okay!

00:15:20.030 --> 00:15:21.070
Rice...

00:15:21.070 --> 00:15:22.830
Y-Yes?

00:15:22.830 --> 00:15:25.210
Quit your bellyaching and run!

00:15:25.720 --> 00:15:28.210
I don't think she understood what I meant!

00:15:28.210 --> 00:15:30.720
Leave me alone, please!

00:15:31.130 --> 00:15:33.940
That's strange! Master usually 
encourages me just like that!

00:15:33.940 --> 00:15:35.490
Never mind! Let's go after her!

00:15:35.490 --> 00:15:36.470
Use this!

00:15:43.140 --> 00:15:44.900
Rice, hold it!

00:15:54.230 --> 00:15:55.990
She's so slippery!

00:15:55.990 --> 00:15:57.870
Get back here!

00:15:58.130 --> 00:16:00.120
Hold it!

00:16:02.860 --> 00:16:04.870
That nimble little...

00:16:04.870 --> 00:16:06.880
Hold it!

00:16:10.220 --> 00:16:11.070
Slip!

00:16:13.530 --> 00:16:15.390
Later

00:16:17.240 --> 00:16:18.140
The battery...

00:16:21.020 --> 00:16:22.180
And that's what happened!

00:16:22.180 --> 00:16:24.520
That is such a mood!

00:16:24.830 --> 00:16:26.410
What do you want to do for the midterm test?

00:16:26.410 --> 00:16:27.020
Run!

00:16:27.020 --> 00:16:27.990
I know, right?

00:16:27.990 --> 00:16:29.160
Rice!

00:16:29.160 --> 00:16:29.770
Rice!

00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:36.830
Hey, Palmer, did you see Rice Shower?

00:16:36.830 --> 00:16:37.870
Rice?

00:16:37.870 --> 00:16:39.560
Nope. Did you, Helios?

00:16:39.560 --> 00:16:40.500
Sure didn't.

00:16:40.500 --> 00:16:42.990
We're looking for her. 
Please let us know if you find her.

00:16:42.990 --> 00:16:43.720
'Kay!

00:16:49.960 --> 00:16:51.710
Rice, huh?

00:16:51.710 --> 00:16:53.360
What's up? Something about her?

00:16:53.360 --> 00:16:55.420
You remember at the Kikkashou?

00:16:55.420 --> 00:16:57.730
Oh, she beat Bourbon! That was so hype!

00:16:57.730 --> 00:17:00.360
A hardcore race between 
two strong horse girls...

00:17:00.360 --> 00:17:03.600
I <i>so</i> want to do something like that!

00:17:03.600 --> 00:17:05.840
How about with me? You wanna take me on?

00:17:05.840 --> 00:17:06.990
You bet I do!

00:17:06.990 --> 00:17:08.790
NGL, we're just gonna run like usual!

00:17:08.790 --> 00:17:10.110
I know, right?!

00:17:25.210 --> 00:17:30.260
Not wanting to run... Do you suppose 
Rice-san has lost her confidence?

00:17:30.260 --> 00:17:32.100
I'm sure that's not it!

00:17:32.100 --> 00:17:34.960
Rice-chan's a really strong horse girl.

00:17:35.210 --> 00:17:37.730
When she locks in on her target,
 she gets so focused!

00:17:37.730 --> 00:17:41.900
Although at the Kikkashou, I think
she was only looking at Bourbon-chan.

00:17:41.900 --> 00:17:46.130
Right, you've raced her a few 
times yourself, haven't you?

00:17:46.130 --> 00:17:48.380
Yep! This is gonna be the seventh time.

00:17:49.410 --> 00:17:53.570
Y'know, she's kind of a big deal to me.

00:17:53.570 --> 00:17:55.440
I feel the same way.

00:17:55.440 --> 00:17:59.740
She demonstrated her strength 
without a doubt at the Nikkei Sho.

00:18:02.770 --> 00:18:04.070
Tracen...

00:18:04.070 --> 00:18:04.570
Fight!

00:18:04.570 --> 00:18:05.010
On!

00:18:05.010 --> 00:18:05.360
Fight!

00:18:05.360 --> 00:18:05.700
On!

00:18:05.700 --> 00:18:06.130
Fight!

00:18:06.130 --> 00:18:06.740
On!

00:18:12.510 --> 00:18:15.430
Is it... okay if I run?

00:18:15.430 --> 00:18:16.970
What're you doing?

00:18:17.190 --> 00:18:18.760
What are <i>you</i> doing?

00:18:18.760 --> 00:18:20.260
I'm gonna try and win the Triple Crown!

00:18:20.260 --> 00:18:22.420
Not gonna happen! Because I'm gonna win it!

00:18:22.420 --> 00:18:23.390
Hey, don't get in my way!

00:18:23.700 --> 00:18:25.390
Yeah, that's right!

00:18:26.590 --> 00:18:28.850
Bourbon! You can win next time!

00:18:28.850 --> 00:18:31.770
Winning the Triple Crown would've 
been cool, but you did a great job!

00:18:31.770 --> 00:18:34.570
I'm still rooting for you!
 I love you, Bourbon!

00:18:34.570 --> 00:18:36.560
You did a good job, Tannhäuser!

00:18:37.780 --> 00:18:40.120
I can't do this anymore...

00:18:40.120 --> 00:18:41.030
Rice!

00:18:42.800 --> 00:18:44.340
We finally found her...

00:18:44.340 --> 00:18:47.120
You don't know when to give up. 
Please, just leave me alone.

00:18:47.120 --> 00:18:48.680
You're the one who didn't give up, Rice!

00:18:48.680 --> 00:18:51.810
You never gave up during the Kikkashou!

00:18:51.810 --> 00:18:53.920
Don't talk to me about the Kikkashou!

00:18:54.910 --> 00:18:57.980
I just wanted people to accept me.

00:18:57.980 --> 00:19:02.650
I thought that if I could beat you, 
Bourbon-san, that they would.

00:19:02.650 --> 00:19:05.430
That's why I tried so hard.

00:19:05.430 --> 00:19:08.860
But nobody wanted me to win.

00:19:08.860 --> 00:19:10.690
And when I did,

00:19:11.200 --> 00:19:14.560
they just got mad, and didn't accept it!

00:19:15.790 --> 00:19:19.110
I'm not like you two.

00:19:20.320 --> 00:19:22.210
I'm a heel.

00:19:23.270 --> 00:19:28.170
People hate me, boo me, 
and then I make them unhappy.

00:19:28.170 --> 00:19:30.540
Even though my name's meant to be a blessing...

00:19:31.080 --> 00:19:32.850
Even though I'm called Rice Shower.

00:19:33.860 --> 00:19:36.960
That's why I won't run anymore.

00:19:37.680 --> 00:19:38.990
Rice...

00:19:38.990 --> 00:19:41.470
Quit your bellyaching and run!

00:19:41.470 --> 00:19:43.410
How can you say that?!

00:19:43.410 --> 00:19:45.370
Because I want you to run.

00:19:45.370 --> 00:19:49.060
I don't understand! How can you say 
that after everything I told you?!

00:19:49.350 --> 00:19:53.640
No one's happy if I run! Even when 
I win, it's just a disappointment!

00:19:53.640 --> 00:19:55.690
There's no point in me running!

00:19:55.690 --> 00:19:57.590
So, why—

00:19:57.590 --> 00:20:00.140
Because you are my hero.

00:20:08.720 --> 00:20:10.830
I'm injured.

00:20:11.370 --> 00:20:12.810
Seriously injured.

00:20:13.890 --> 00:20:16.540
There have been times when I've 
been overwhelmed with anxiety

00:20:16.540 --> 00:20:19.500
about whether I'd get to run again.

00:20:20.930 --> 00:20:23.590
I was unable to meet my 
Master's expectations.

00:20:23.910 --> 00:20:27.100
I even considered giving up on racing.

00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:31.750
Bourbon... I pushed you too hard.

00:20:32.840 --> 00:20:33.820
I'm sorry.

00:20:40.850 --> 00:20:46.430
But I never gave up because of you, Rice.

00:20:44.360 --> 00:20:46.860
Winning Horse Girl

00:20:44.360 --> 00:20:46.860
Horse Girl of the Kikkashou
Up Close With Rice Shower

00:20:50.870 --> 00:20:52.370
{\an3}Up Close With the Winner of the Kikkashou, Rice Shower!
<font size="13">She Had Her Sights Set on Mihono Bourbon</font>

00:20:50.870 --> 00:20:52.370
{\an7}"They Call Her the Assassin in Black!"
Rice Shower's
 Racing Future

00:20:52.690 --> 00:20:55.870
Next time, I want to win. 
I don't want to lose again.

00:20:55.870 --> 00:20:58.110
I want to race a strong opponent, like you.

00:20:58.110 --> 00:21:02.200
I've been able to work hard at 
my recovery because of that goal.

00:21:04.560 --> 00:21:07.420
It's true that you took my dream.

00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:11.270
But the hope and new dream you've 
given me are worth more than that.

00:21:11.780 --> 00:21:13.180
Bourbon-san...

00:21:14.030 --> 00:21:17.520
You're not a heel. You're a hero.

00:21:18.400 --> 00:21:21.050
I'm... a hero?

00:21:22.190 --> 00:21:23.530
Bourbon...

00:21:23.530 --> 00:21:27.030
And yet you came in eighth 
place at the Arima Kinen?!

00:21:26.170 --> 00:21:27.030
Placed 11th at Arima

00:21:27.030 --> 00:21:30.650
You're my hero! You're a strong horse girl!

00:21:30.650 --> 00:21:33.160
You have to run in the 
Tennoushou to prove that!

00:21:47.480 --> 00:21:50.130
Stop being so selfish.

00:21:50.600 --> 00:21:51.930
I'm sorry.

00:21:51.930 --> 00:21:54.780
You can say all that, but it's 
just more trouble for me.

00:21:57.170 --> 00:21:58.110
But...

00:21:58.740 --> 00:22:01.850
I understand how you feel, Bourbon-san.

00:22:02.830 --> 00:22:05.690
I'm going to try again.

00:22:09.090 --> 00:22:11.450
I'm still scared, but...

00:22:13.320 --> 00:22:14.110
Right.

00:22:14.720 --> 00:22:18.850
I want to run with you too,
 Bourbon-san. So...

00:22:22.580 --> 00:22:25.560
I'm going to enter the Tennoushou!

